dct_title_s: A MAP OF THE WORLD Shewing the Course of Capt. Cook’s (sic) Voyage Round the same
dct_description_sm: California shown with two deep northern bays, and unlabeled except as California. S. of Annian to the north and C. Patientia to the northwest.
Track taken by Edward Cooke and Woodes Rogers from 1709-1711 shown. Cooke accompanied Woodes Rogers on his privateering voyage around the world.

Issued in: A voyage to the South Sea, and round the World / By Capt. Edward Cooke. -- London : Printed by H.M. for B. Lintot and R. Gosling in Fleet-Street, A. Bettesworth on London-Bridge, and W. Innys in St. Paul’s Church-Yard. MDCCXII. (1712). Map bound into the front of the book facing the title page.
